<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

						Short Form of the Metacognitions Questionnaire (MCQ-30)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 02-20-2018
last updated:  02-24-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-24-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements a computerized version of the Short Form of the Metacognitions Questionnaire (MCQ-30) 
as described in:

Wells, A., & Cartwright-Hatton, S. (2004). A short form of the metacognitions questionnaire:
Properties of the MCQ-30. Behaviour Research and Therapy, 42(4), 385-396. doi:10.1016/S0005-7967(03)00147-5

Long Form of the Metacognitions Questionnaire (MCQ):

Cartwright-Hatton, S., & Wells, A. (1997). Beliefs about worry and intrusions: the metacognitions 
questionnaire and its correlates. Journal of Anxiety Disorders, 11, 279–296.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
30 4-point likert scale, self-report

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 3 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'mcq_30_survey.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								Scale: 1 (do not agree) - 4 (agree very much)
								no reversed scored questions
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)
								

(2) Summary data file: 'mcq_30_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

Score Interpretation: higher scores => higher levels of unhelpful metacognition

Total:	sum of all responses (score range: 30-120)
zTotal: z-score of Total Score with Mean = 48.41, SD = 13.31 (see Wells & Cartwright-Hatton, 2004, Table 1, p.389)
pTotal: percentile rank of z-score

Subscales are calculated by summing the following items (score range: 6-24): 

cognitiveConfidence (lack of)= sum of (q8,q14,q17,q24,q26,q29)
zCognitiveConfidence: z-score with Mean = 9.51, SD = 4.06 (see Wells & Cartwright-Hatton, 2004, Table 1, p.389)
pCognitiveConfidence: percentile rank of z-score

positiveBeliefs (about worry)=sum of (q1,q7,q10,q19,q23,q28)
zPositiveBeliefs: z-score with Mean = 9.60, SD = 3.46 (see Wells & Cartwright-Hatton, 2004, Table 1, p.389)
pPositiveBeliefs: percentile rank of z-score

cognitiveSelfConsciousness = sum of (q3,q5,q12,q16,q18,q30)
zCognitiveSelfConsciousness: z-score with Mean 11.65, SD = 4.68 (see Wells & Cartwright-Hatton, 2004, Table 1, p.389)
pCognitiveSelfConsciousness: percentile rank of z-score

uncontrollabilityDanger (negative beliefs about) = sum of (q2,q4,q9,q11,q15,q21)
zUncontrollabilityDanger: z-score with Mean = 9.30, SD = 4.00 (see Wells & Cartwright-Hatton, 2004, Table 1, p.389)
pUncontrollabilityDanger: percentile rank of z-score

needControlThoughts = sum of (q6,q13,q20,q22,q25,q27)
zNeedControlThoughts: z-score with Mean = 8.34, SD = 2.62 (see Wells & Cartwright-Hatton, 2004, Table 1, p.389)
pNeedControlThoughts: percentile rank of z-score

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
slightly adapted from Cartwright-Hatton & Wells, A. (1997), see section Editable Parameters

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "This questionnaire is concerned with beliefs people have about their thinking. Listed below are a number of beliefs that people have expressed. Please read each item and indicate how much you generally agree with it.

Please respond to all the items, there are no right or wrong answers.
"
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.00%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</instruct>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform,script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed,
expressions.Total, expressions.zTotal, expressions.pTotal,
expressions.cognitiveConfidence, expressions.zCognitiveConfidence, expressions.pCognitiveConfidence,
expressions.positiveBeliefs, expressions.zPositiveBeliefs, expressions.pPositiveBeliefs,
expressions.cognitiveSelfConsciousness, expressions.zCognitiveSelfConsciousness, expressions.pCognitiveSelfConsciousness,
expressions.uncontrollabilityDanger, expressions.zUncontrollabilityDanger, expressions.pUncontrollabilityDanger,
expressions.needControlThoughts, expressions.zNeedControlThoughts, expressions.pNeedControlThoughts)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<expressions>
/cognitiveConfidence = radiobuttons.q8_cc.response + radiobuttons.q14_cc.response + radiobuttons.q17_cc.response +
radiobuttons.q24_cc.response + radiobuttons.q26_cc.response + radiobuttons.q29_cc.response
/positiveBeliefs=radiobuttons.q1_pb.response + radiobuttons.q7_pb.response + radiobuttons.q10_pb.response +
radiobuttons.q19_pb.response + radiobuttons.q23_pb.response + radiobuttons.q28_pb.response
/cognitiveSelfConsciousness = radiobuttons.q3_cs.response + radiobuttons.q5_cs.response + radiobuttons.q12_cs.response +
radiobuttons.q16_cs.response + radiobuttons.q18_cs.response + radiobuttons.q30_cs.response
/uncontrollabilityDanger = radiobuttons.q2_ud.response + radiobuttons.q4_ud.response + radiobuttons.q9_ud.response +
radiobuttons.q11_ud.response + radiobuttons.q15_ud.response + radiobuttons.q21_ud.response
/needControlThoughts = radiobuttons.q6_ct.response + radiobuttons.q13_ct.response + radiobuttons.q20_ct.response +
radiobuttons.q22_ct.response + radiobuttons.q25_ct.response + radiobuttons.q27_ct.response

/Total = expressions.cognitiveConfidence + expressions.positiveBeliefs + expressions.cognitiveSelfConsciousness +
expressions.uncontrollabilityDanger + expressions.needControlThoughts


/zCognitiveConfidence = (expressions.cognitiveConfidence - 9.51)/4.06
/zPositiveBeliefs = (expressions.positiveBeliefs - 9.60)/3.46
/zCognitiveSelfConsciousness = (expressions.cognitiveSelfConsciousness - 11.65)/4.68
/zUncontrollabilityDanger = (expressions.uncontrollabilityDanger - 9.30)/4.00
/zNeedControlThoughts = (expressions.needControlThoughts - 8.34)/2.62

/zTotal = (expressions.Total - 48.41)/13.31

/pCognitiveConfidence = pofz(expressions.zCognitiveConfidence)
/pPositiveBeliefs = pofz(expressions.zPositiveBeliefs)
/pCognitiveSelfConsciousness = pofz(expressions.zCognitiveSelfConsciousness)
/pUncontrollabilityDanger = pofz(expressions.zUncontrollabilityDanger)
/pNeedControlThoughts = pofz(expressions.zNeedControlThoughts)
/pTotal = pofz(expressions.zTotal)
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1_pb>
/caption = "1. Worrying helps me to avoid future problems."
/ options = ("Do not agree", "Agree slightly", "Agree moderately   ", "Agree very much")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2_ud>
/caption = "2. My worrying is dangerous for me."
/ options = ("Do not agree", "Agree slightly", "Agree moderately   ", "Agree very much")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3_cs>
/caption = "3. I think a lot about my thoughts."
/ options = ("Do not agree", "Agree slightly", "Agree moderately   ", "Agree very much")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4_ud>
/caption = "4. I could make myself sick with worrying."
/ options = ("Do not agree", "Agree slightly", "Agree moderately   ", "Agree very much")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

*
<radiobuttons q5_cs>
/caption = "5. I am aware of the way my mind works when I am thinking through a problem."
/ options = ("Do not agree", "Agree slightly", "Agree moderately   ", "Agree very much")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6_ct>
/caption = "6. If I did not control a worrying thought and then it happened, it would be my fault."
/ options = ("Do not agree", "Agree slightly", "Agree moderately   ", "Agree very much")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7_pb>
/caption = "7. I need to worry in order to remain organized."
/ options = ("Do not agree", "Agree slightly", "Agree moderately   ", "Agree very much")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8_cc>
